comments.body:
The one liner referred by [~dshekhawat] is 
{code:none}
for x in `ip addr show | grep 178. | awk '{print $2}'|sed 's:/32::'`; do /tmp/arping -c 2 -U -I bond1 $x; done
{code}

The arping used there is the same as the one found in the package _iputils-arping_ on Debian. The version (again in Debian) called _arping_ do not have the _-U_ options used above. 

[~juphoff], not sure how much progress have you done already, but if you need help [~mdshaonimran], [~dfederlein] and I could help to produce a patch if you care.
